  "text": "The G1 garbage collector's concurrent marking and mixed collection cycle chain in openjdk/jdk is implemented through a coordinated sequence of C++ classes and functions:\n\n## G1ConcurrentMark Start Trigger\n\nThe concurrent marking cycle is initiated in `g1ConcurrentMarkThread.cpp:run_service()` (line 115), which serves as the main entry point for the concurrent marking thread. This function enters a loop that calls `concurrent_cycle_start()` (line 125) to register GC timer and tracer events, defined in `g1ConcurrentMark.cpp:concurrent_cycle_start()` (line 1114).\n\n## Concurrent Marking Main Loop\n\nThe marking cycle orchestration happens in `g1ConcurrentMarkThread.cpp:concurrent_mark_cycle_do()` (line 271), which executes the following phases:\n1. **Phase 1 - Root Region Scanning**: Scans the root regions to identify initial reachable objects\n2. **Phase 2 - Mark Loop**: `phase_mark_loop()` (line 178) which includes:\n   - `subphase_mark_from_roots()` (line 214) that calls `g1ConcurrentMark.cpp:mark_from_roots()` (line 1145)\n   - This spawns concurrent marking tasks that populate the global mark stack\n\n## SATB Marking Queue Processing\n\nDuring the marking process, the SATB (Snapshot-At-The-Beginning) marking queue buffers are processed by `g1ConcurrentMark.cpp:G1CMTask::drain_satb_buffers()` (line 2424). This function:\n- Iterates over completed SATB buffers from the queue set `g1SATBMarkQueueSet.cpp` (line 35)\n- Applies a closure to each buffer entry to determine if objects require marking\n- Filters entries using the requirements defined in `g1SATBMarkQueueSet.cpp` (lines 82-100) which check if objects were allocated before marking started\n\nThe SATB queue set is initialized in `g1SATBMarkQueueSet.cpp:G1SATBMarkQueueSet::G1SATBMarkQueueSet()` (line 35) and manages per-thread marking buffers.\n\n## Remembered Set Scanning\n\nRemembered set management is implemented in `g1HeapRegionRemSet.cpp` (line 1 onwards) which defines the remembered set data structures for each heap region. The actual scanning of remembered sets during evacuation phases is coordinated through `g1RemSet.cpp`, which contains the `G1RemSetScanState` class (line 89) that:\n- Maintains card table scanning state across regions\n- Distributes work in chunks to parallel workers\n- Tracks which regions and chunks contain cards to be scanned\n- Manages the merging of card sources (dirty cards, remembered set cards)\n\n## Region Liveness and Candidate Selection\n\nAfter the marking completes, `phase_rebuild_and_scrub()` (line 240 in g1ConcurrentMarkThread.cpp) triggers the rebuild of remembered sets. The cleanup phase (`phase_cleanup()` line 253) invokes `VM_G1PauseCleanup` which executes the selection of regions for mixed collection.\n\nThe critical mixed collection region selection happens through `g1CollectionSetChooser.cpp:G1CollectionSetChooser::build()` (line 262), which:\n1. Creates a `G1BuildCandidateRegionsTask` (line 39 in g1CollectionSetChooser.cpp)\n2. Processes each old/humongous region in parallel using `G1BuildCandidateRegionsClosure::do_heap_region()` (line 145)\n3. Evaluates regions based on:\n   - Whether they are old regions (line 148)\n   - Whether they have tracked remembered sets (line 154)\n   - Occupancy constraints using `region_occupancy_low_enough_for_evac()` (line 166)\n4. Sorts candidate regions by reclaimable bytes (line 250)\n5. Prunes regions based on garbage collection efficiency thresholds (line 251)\n6. Populates the collection set candidates using `G1CollectionSetCandidates::set_candidates_from_marking()` (line 252)\n\n## Region Liveness Statistics\n\nThe liveness of regions is determined by `G1UpdateRegionLivenessAndSelectForRebuildTask` (line 1203 in g1ConcurrentMark.cpp) which:\n- Updates per-region liveness information based on concurrent marking statistics\n- Reclaims empty regions immediately\n- Selects regions for remembered set rebuild\n- Processes both humongous and old regions to update their top-at-rebuild-start pointers\n\nThis complete chain ensures that the G1 garbage collector efficiently identifies regions for evacuation during mixed collection pauses based on accurate liveness information gathered during concurrent marking."
